cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with medium access control protocols in the context of a slotted random access network, which is a typical problem in the field of computer networks and communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also introduces performance metrics and formulates the problem of finding an optimal protocol, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper applies the framework to wireless local area networks (WLANs), which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
